 U.S. Courts, Classified Documents Reveal</h4></a></div><div class="RelatedPosts-promo" data-reactid="282"><a href="https://theintercept.com/2018/09/17/journalists-fisa-court-spying/" data-reactid="283"><div class="RelatedPosts-promo-link-thumbnail" data-reactid="284"><img height="440" src="https://theintercept-static.imgix.net/usq/7eddea91-5c49-497e-94f1-ae930a9bf9e9/7eddea91-5c49-497e-94f1-ae930a9bf9e9.bin?auto=compress,format&amp;cs=srgb&amp;dpr=2&amp;h=440&amp;w=440&amp;fit=crop&amp;crop=faces%2Cedges&amp;_=be28f284437a424ab4df3866a7cc18ad" width="440" data-reactid="285"/></div><h4 class="RelatedPosts-promo-link-title" data-reactid="286">Government Can Spy on Journalists in the U.S. Using Invasive Foreign Intelligence Process</h4></a></div></div><div class="Post-latest-articles" data-reactid="287"><h4 class="Post-latest-articles-header" data-reactid="288">Latest Stories</h4><div class="Promo-container" data-reactid="289"><div data-reactid="290"></div><div class="Promo Promo--default Promo--video" data-reactid="291"><a class="Promo-link" href="/2020/04/18/trump-latin-america-foreign-policy-joe-biden/" data-reactid="292"><div class="GridRow" data-reactid="293"><div class="Promo-image-container" data-reactid="294"><div class="Promo-image-block" data-reactid="295"><div class="ResponsiveImage Promo-image" style="padding-top:50%;" data-reactid="296"><noscript data-reactid="297"><img src="https://theintercept-static.imgix.net/usq/68115254-b698-4c8d-93e3-ae18f013e128/68115254-b698-4c8d-93e3-ae18f013e128.bin?auto=compress,format&cs=srgb&dpr=2&h=450&w=900&fit=crop&crop=faces%2Cedges&_=96d69908306e5168585e8e7a6f71fecb" alt="null" class="ResponsiveImage-image" height="900" width="1800"></noscript></div></div></div><div class="Promo-text" data-reactid="298"><div class="PromoVideoPlayButton Promo-playButton Promo-playButton--in-title" data-reactid="299"></div><div class="Promo-title-block" data-reactid="300"><h4 class="Promo-title" data-reactid="301"><span class="Promo-title-